
Given an array of n integers to check if there exist integer m >= 2
such that for every ai % m will make the all array equal.
Solution : check if the gcd difference is greater than 1.


In Maximum subarray sum problems check if the empty arrays are allowed because if it is not
the neutral value of node is not (sum = pre = suf = ans = 0)
it will be (sum = 0 , pre = suf = ans = -infLL)

Some problem depend on that the operation described will acur few number of times
so always when you see a new operation check its limits





